<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="131" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,901,1214]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1009,1034]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wingspan 15.0–18.0 mm. The forewing is broader and darker than in other species with similar pattern. The hindwing is dark grey, with a rounded concavity before the anal corner. In the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1346,1427,1045,1070]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 29" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1312,1335]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1288]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1291]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 29. Male genitalia of Conaspasia n. gen. 27. C. albonigra (Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak) (slide NHMO 2242). 28. C. congolana n. sp. (slide L. Aarvik 2013.011). 29. C. sophrona (Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak) (slide L. Aarvik 2013.013). Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226771/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">
Fig. 
<number box="[1398,1427,1046,1070]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
) the broad uncus has spines, and the very long phallus are characteristic. The female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1296,1081,1106]" captionStart="FIGURES 36, 37" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1623,1646]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,375,1598]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[216,1371,375,1602]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 36, 37. Female genitalia of Conaspasia n. gen. 36. C. albonigra (Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak) (slide NHMO 2243). 37. C. sophrona (Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak) (slide L. Aarvik 2013.014). Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226774/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">
Fig. 
<number box="[1267,1296,1082,1106]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
) differ from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[247,390,1117,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Conaspasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albonigra">
<emphasis box="[247,390,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">C. albonigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the ductus seminalis arising from the ductus bursae far from corpus bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
